<section>
  <p>
    Spellblade is a tabletop roleplaying game set in a gritty, low-fantasy medieval world. 
    Built around a d100 system, it keeps outcomes precise and consequences real — combat is 
    deadly, resources matter, and nothing is guaranteed.
  </p>
  <p>
    Rather than locking players into classes or levels, Spellblade uses a fully open 
    progression system. Characters grow through the choices they make — the gear they carry, 
    the skills they develop, and the spells they craft. A modular spell creation system lets 
    players build their own spells from the ground up, combining effects, ranges, and 
    conditions to create something uniquely theirs rather than picking from a preset list.
  </p>
  <p>
    Armour works the same way — layered and modular, each piece providing different 
    protection with real tradeoffs in weight, mobility, and coverage. A full suit of plate 
    will stop most blows, but you'll feel every pound of it. Gear defines your character 
    as much as any stat.
  </p>
  <p>
    Spellblade was built for players who want a system with genuine depth — one that rewards 
    preparation, creativity, and smart play — without drowning in unnecessary complexity.
  </p>
</section>

